@startuml Seq04_ExpenseCategorization
!theme plain
participant User
participant "Frontend" as Frontend
participant "Backend\nCateg. API" as Backend
participant "Rule Engine" as RuleEngine
participant "User Learning\nDB" as LearningDB
participant "LLM API" as LLM
participant "MySQL DB" as DB

autonumber

Note over User,DB: **LEVEL 1: RULE-BASED CATEGORIZATION**

Backend -> RuleEngine: categorize(description="McDonald's")

RuleEngine -> RuleEngine: Load keyword rules
Note over RuleEngine: food_keywords = ["mcdonalds", "kfc", "zomato", "restaurant"]

RuleEngine -> RuleEngine: Check if description matches
alt Match Found
    RuleEngine -> RuleEngine: category_id = 1 (Food)
    RuleEngine --> Backend: {category: "Food", method: "rule",\nconfidence: 0.95}
else No Match
    RuleEngine --> Backend: {category: null, method: "no_match"}
end

Backend -> Frontend: {suggested_category: "Food", confidence: 0.95}
Frontend -> Frontend: Show suggestion
Frontend --> User: Display "Food" as category

Note over User,DB: **USER CORRECTION & LEARNING**

alt Category Incorrect
    User -> Frontend: Change category to "Education"
    Frontend -> Frontend: Show category dropdown
    User -> Frontend: Select Education
    User -> Frontend: Click Save
    
    Frontend -> Backend: PUT /transactions/{id}\n{category_id: 3}
    
    Backend -> DB: UPDATE transactions\nSET category_id=3\nWHERE id={id}
    DB --> Backend: {success}
    
    Note over Backend: **STORE LEARNING PATTERN**
    Backend -> LearningDB: Learn correction
    Backend -> Backend: Extract merchant from description
    Backend -> LearningDB: INSERT INTO user_learning\n(user_id, merchant="Amazon",\ncategory_id=3, frequency=1)
    
    LearningDB --> Backend: {learned}
    
    Backend -> RuleEngine: Update merchant_to_category map
    RuleEngine -> RuleEngine: Amazon Books → Education (user preference)
    
    Backend --> Frontend: {status: "category_updated"}
    Frontend -> Frontend: Show success
    Frontend --> User: Category updated & system learned
end

Note over User,DB: **LEVEL 3: AI FALLBACK (UNKNOWN TRANSACTION)**

Backend -> RuleEngine: categorize(description="ALBAIK DMM BRANCH")

RuleEngine -> RuleEngine: Check rules
alt No Rule Match
    RuleEngine --> Backend: {category: null}
    
    Note over Backend: **FALLBACK TO AI**
    Backend -> LearningDB: Check user_learning for "ALBAIK"
    LearningDB --> Backend: {found: false}
    
    Backend -> LLM: Send to LLM API
    Backend -> LLM: Prompt: "Categorize: ALBAIK DMM BRANCH"
    
    LLM -> LLM: Process with LLM model
    LLM --> Backend: {category: "Food", confidence: 0.87}
    
    Backend -> LearningDB: Cache AI result
    Backend -> LearningDB: INSERT INTO user_learning\n(merchant="ALBAIK",\ncategory_id=1, frequency=1,\nconfidence=0.87)
    
    Backend -> Frontend: {suggested_category: "Food",\nmethod: "ai", confidence: 0.87}
    
    Frontend -> Frontend: Show AI suggestion
    Frontend --> User: Suggested category: Food (AI)
    
    alt User Accepts
        User -> Frontend: Accept Food
        Frontend -> Backend: Confirm category
        Backend -> LearningDB: Increment frequency for ALBAIK→Food
        LearningDB -> LearningDB: frequency += 1
    else User Corrects
        User -> Frontend: Change to other category
        Frontend -> Backend: Save correction
        Backend -> LearningDB: Update learning with user correction
    end
end

Note over User,DB: **BATCH CATEGORIZATION FOR UPLOAD**

Backend -> Backend: categorize_transactions([])

loop For Each Transaction in Batch
    Backend -> RuleEngine: categorize(transaction.description)
    alt Rule Match
        RuleEngine --> Backend: {category, method: "rule"}
    else Check Learning
        Backend -> LearningDB: Query user_learning
        LearningDB --> Backend: {category, frequency}
        alt High Confidence
            Backend -> Backend: Use learned category
        else Low Confidence
            Backend -> LLM: Use AI
        end
    end
end

Backend -> DB: Bulk insert categorized transactions
DB --> Backend: {rows_inserted}

Backend --> Frontend: Summary

Note over User,DB: **PERFORMANCE OPTIMIZATION**

Note over Backend: Caching Strategy:
Note over Backend: - Cache rule keywords in memory
Note over Backend: - Cache learning DB locally
Note over Backend: - Batch LLM calls (every 5 unknowns)
Note over Backend: - Cache LLM results

Backend -> Backend: Monitor API costs
Note over Backend: Cost Reduction:
Note over Backend: - 80% from rules (free)
Note over Backend: - 15% from learning (cached)
Note over Backend: - 5% from AI (paid)

@enduml
